article.headline: Winston-Salem 105, Md.-Eastern Shore 59
article.story: WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. (AP) -- Jamal Durham scored a season-high 25 points as Winston-Salem State ran away with a 103-57 victory over Maryland-Eastern Shore Saturday night. The Rams (6-7) broke to a 12-2 lead in the opening minutes on the way to their second straight win. It was their first 100-point performance since a 103-80 win over Knoxville on Dec. 2, 2005. Winston-Salem head coach Bobby Collins also captured his ninth victory over UMES without a loss. Darrell Wonge scored 18 points, Isiah Tucker had 16 and Brian Fisher added 12 for the Rams. Ed Tyson scored 21 points for the Hawks (2-13).
